Project Modularization Description (PMD)

This refactor reorganizes the SISP codebase into a layered package structure that separates orchestration, data IO, preprocessing transforms, anomaly modeling, and shared utilities without changing model behavior. Configuration values now live in config/settings.py, all artifact path creation is centralized in sisp/utils/paths.py, and runtime checks/logging are handled through sisp/utils/validation.py and sisp/utils/logger.py. Pipeline entrypoints in pipelines/ are intentionally thin: they discover channels, call module functions in sequence, and write summaries. Domain logic is split by responsibility: sisp/io/ handles dataset download/load and artifact persistence, sisp/preprocessing/ contains channel splitting, metadata masks, imputation, variance handling, winsorization, and scaling, and sisp/anomaly/ contains SVD rank selection, reconstruction scoring, thresholding, prediction, and evaluation reporting. This structure improves maintainability, testability, and future extensibility while keeping outputs deterministic and backward-compatible.
